<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>CSS Grid Layout Test: Minimum size of grid items</title>
<link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-grid-1/#min-size-auto" rel="help" title="6.5. Implied Minimum Size of Grid Items" />
<link href="reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square.xht" rel="match" />
<meta content="Checks that automatic minimum size gets clamped, so the grid item doesn't overflow the fixed size area." name="assert" />
<style>
#reference-overlapped-red {
    position: absolute;
    background-color: red;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    z-index: -1;
}

#constrained-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid: 100px / 100px;
}

#test-grid-item-overlapping-green {
    background-color: green;
}

#content-200x200 {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
}
</style>

</head><body><p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>

<div id="reference-overlapped-red"></div>
<div id="constrained-grid">
    <div id="test-grid-item-overlapping-green">
        <div id="content-200x200"></div>
    </div>
</div>
</body></html>